This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with speech recognition and enhancement. It may also belong to the sub-category of Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) as it involves processing audio data. Additionally, it could be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it uses neural network models. It may also fall under Signal Processing (cs.SP) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves processing and analyzing audio data for transcription.
